                <h1 class="text-center text-primary mb-4">Attandence Management System</h1>
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h4 class="section-title">Technology Stack</h4>
                    <p>ASP.NET, C#, HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, SQL Server</p>
                </div>
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h4 class="section-title">Project Overview</h4>
                    <p>
                        I developed a comprehensive Inventory Management System to streamline the management of product stock, orders, and reports.
                        This system addresses the critical needs of inventory tracking and control, offering businesses a reliable solution for efficient 
                        operations and data-driven decision-making.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h4 class="section-title">Key Highlights</h4>
                    <ul class="list-group">
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>User Interface:</strong> The system’s front-end was designed using HTML, CSS, and Bootstrap, delivering a responsive 
                            and intuitive user interface. The design ensures compatibility across desktops, tablets, and smartphones, providing a
                            seamless experience. With user-friendly navigation and visually appealing layouts, the interface allows users to interact 
                            with the system effortlessly, improving overall productivity.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Backend Development:</strong> The backend was developed using ASP.NET and C#, ensuring a robust and scalable architecture.
                            The use of ASP.NET facilitated the integration of essential business logic, while C# enabled efficient handling of processes like inventory updates,
                            order management, and automated alerts. The backend design also ensures maintainability and supports future feature enhancements.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Database:</strong> The system employs SQL Server as the database, ensuring reliable and efficient data storage.
                            Key database functionalities include:.
                            <ul class="list-group">
                                <li class="list-group-item">
                                    <strong>Product Management: </strong>Maintaining product details, including name, category, price, and stock levels.
                                </li>
                                <li class="list-group-item">
                                    <strong>Order Management:</strong>Recording and processing customer orders in real time.
                                </li>
                                <li class="list-group-item">
                                    <strong>Transaction History: </strong> Storing a detailed history of inventory transactions for auditing and reporting purposes.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h4 class="section-title">Core Features</h4>
                    <ul class="list-group">
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>User Authentication:</strong> Secure login with role-based access control.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Product Categorization:</strong> Organizes products into categories for better searchability and management.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Real-Time Updates:</strong> Allows users to view current stock levels and updates automatically as transactions occur.
                            Provides insights into inventory trends to optimize stock management.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Order Management:</strong>Simplifies the process of creating, tracking, and fulfilling orders.
                            Automatically updates stock levels upon order completion.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Automated Alert:</strong> Sends notifications to administrators for low stock levels, ensuring timely restocking and preventing shortages.
                        </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Reporting and Analytics:</strong>Generates detailed reports on stock status, order history, and inventory trends to support data-driven decisions.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h4 class="section-title">Security Measures</h4>
                    <ul class="list-group">
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <Strong>Role-Based Access Control:</Strong> Implemented secure authentication and authorization mechanisms, restricting access to sensitive data and features based on user roles (e.g., administrators, staff).
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <Strong>Data Validation:</Strong> Applied client-side and server-side validation to ensure the integrity of user input and prevent vulnerabilities like SQL injection.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <Strong>Encrypted Transactions:</Strong> Secured sensitive data, including user credentials and transaction details, with encryption protocols.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h4 class="section-title">Outcome</h4>
